        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12727948/comment/14100874",
            "id": "14100874",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "YARN-1867 has added queue ACL checks, and hasAccess is already invoked by getApp and getApps api's. If queue ACL access is available, then information of an application such as *start/finished/elapsed time* and *AM container information* will be filled in to AppInfo object.\nDo you mean some more extra information is taken from customized yarn filter added in YARN-2247, could you please help to give some more insight.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2014-08-18T17:13:55.186+0000",
            "updated": "2014-08-18T17:13:55.186+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12727948/comment/14100883",
            "id": "14100883",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=zjshen",
              "name": "zjshen",
              "key": "zjshen",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10443",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10443",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10443",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10443"
              },
              "displayName": "Zhijie Shen",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Thanks for notifying me of that. Would you please check the other app-related getter methods? For example, getAppAttempts. It seems that we can access without any access control.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=zjshen",
              "name": "zjshen",
              "key": "zjshen",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10443",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10443",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10443",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10443"
              },
              "displayName": "Zhijie Shen",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2014-08-18T17:23:39.190+0000",
            "updated": "2014-08-18T17:23:39.190+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12727948/comment/14100963",
            "id": "14100963",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Yes. getAppAttempts and getAppState could also fall in to this ACL check. Only problem is, *getAppAttempts* does not have \"HttpServletRequest hsr Context\". \n{code}  public AppAttemptsInfo getAppAttempts(@PathParam(\"appid\") String appId){code}\nHence getting UGI information without HttpServletRequest  is not possible for getAppAttempts api.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
